GnbDgcHs,Add new Tasmota value to Home Assistan via MQTT config topic message,ottelo15,JSON,Thursday 28th of March 2024 09:20:50 AM CDT,"== How to transfer a new Tasmota value from your Tasmota Script to Home Assistant ==
You can use MQTT Discovery in HA to add sensors and other entities that are not discovered through Tasmota integration and associate them with an already discovered device.
1) add a new line of code inside your script
2) Install and start MQTT Explorer in HA
3) Look for your new MQTT sensor inside MQTT Explorer e.g. stat/%topic%/script/ yieldday = xxx kWh
4) Publish a new config topic to Home Assistant with MQTT Explorer. Home Assistant will then automatically add the sensor to the already published device.
5) Click on topic ""homeassistant/sensor"". On right side click on ""homeassistant/sensor"" below ""Publish"". Change the topic address to e.g. ""homeassistant/sensor/mt175/yieldday/config""

6) Then paste the following JSON code into the field and activate the retain flag. Change or add mqtt config variables if needed (use abbreviations to keep everything short, see url above). A020A61AFAD3 is the MAC of Tasmota and tasmota_1AFAD3 the topic + last part of MAC. Change it!
